asses through their server. Users can select to automatically delete content, but is there any risk? We reached out to Jotform regarding their encryption and how this works:nI was wondering what transfer mechanism was used to get files from jotform to google drive?nOur integration is using API to forward files to Google Drive. All form submissions are using SSL. It is made on 256-bit SSL secure connection. Our servers are located on SSAE16 Audited facilities.nHere''''s a helpful guide: https:--www.jotform.com-help-192-How-to-Integrate-a-Form-with-Google-DrivenAlso is there a way to automatically delete form submissions after they''''ve been submitted?nYes, you can use the Auto Delete Submissions App. This app deletes new form submissions instantly as soon as they are received. Here''''s the link: https:--auto-delete.jotform.io-nnCDHS is asking for OIT''''s review of this potential solution.','Open','CDHS','Cindy Mastin','2017-02-06 00:00:00','CA Service Desk ticket',null,'','Assigned',null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,'Steve Maas','Steven.Maas@state.co.us','9abfe6a9589949f8931fdcdf884c5ab6','2017-02-07 00:00:00','David Coe','david.coe@state.co.us','b40056defd4c4ad7a71ed3507993dc6d','Solution Options','Assigned',10,'2017-02-28 00:00:00',null,'2017-02-09 22:48:20','7c003c7f720b4f06be2dd2f4a657e788','9abfe6a9589949f8931fdcdf884c5ab6','772c3fb23cb3417bbde2d200fa6322ba',null,null,null);
